			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">An idea to ease four song twisting<a name="62208"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 4:48 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span> I have an idea that could make twisting four songs much easier.  This will be especially beneficial to those who don't have a top of the line computer and have lag issues. I don't believe you should be penalized for not having the latest and best computer.
<br />

<br />
 When I group I try to keep four songs up during battle and I hate to see icons drop if I loose my twist rhythm or get some lag. I concentrate so hard on keeping my songs up that I often miss things in my chat box and it takes some of the fun out of the game.
<br />

<br />
 My solution is change all 3 tick songs to 4 ticks (don't shut me off yet it gets better). This would make keeping four songs up effortless even under laggy conditions. 
<br />

<br />
 The intention is to ease twisting and not to allow Bards to twist in extra songs. So heres the catch to balance it out.  You will only be allowed to have four songs up at once. If you try to twist in a fifth song then the song that was running longest will drop when the  fifth song takes effect.
<br />
 
<br />
 Some exceptions to the rule would be that 1 minute duration songs would not aply to the four song rule. You would be able to slow with RoT and still twist four songs or twist four DoTs and also use the 1 minute Angstlich's Assonance.
<br />

<br />
 Also the 2 1/2 minute Selo's would always be usable but the other run songs would change to 4 ticks and follow the new rules.
<br />

<br />
 Some issues still need to be worked out regarding clicky items but basically if the effect icon goes in the spell buff window then it will always be usable. If it has a cast time and acts like a regular song like on WDotR then the four song rule aplies. If its an insta click item like LoFW then it would be usable with four other songs because I believe the intention of insta click items is to allow another song to be twisted in.
<br />

<br />
 You could also ease twisting by reducing casting times and still following these rules but there may be other advantages to fast casting and the idea here is to ease twisting while not adding powers or abilities that don't already exist. I don't belive that this system would allow a Bards to do anything more than they can now but will make it a little less stressful.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
