				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Wouldn't really work =/<a name="62222"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 5:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Unfortunatly I like the ideas above but not really able to implement imho.  I read all of the first post... 4 tick duration and only allowing 4 song buffs? *thinks raid situation* I have 5+ song buffs in that situation, this &quot;benefit&quot; wouldn't benefit us, unless they made it recognize bard songs being sung by other bards then yes a benefit, but then people would complain &quot;OMFGZ HE CAN TWIST 6 SONGS ON A MOB&quot;  (be it dots or DD song, you could in theory place 6 songs (not including the longer duration dot songs.)
<br />

<br />
I find myself dropping songs if i talk to others in party/guild/tell&quot; however usually only drops to 3 song twist, still able to pull easily etc and cc, just 3 songs instead of 4, or I just use bard speech... consisting of 4-10 word sentences lmao my friends always laugh when I send tells like this cause they know im twisting while talking.
<br />

<br />
I do like the auto twist idea, would be nice... though id like it implemented where you can select which song you want the twist to start in, meaning say you stopped the auto twist on song 2, you could pick up again on say song 3 or song 4, not start over on song 1.  Though that brings us back to something i have always hated, I hate when I see 3 songs being twisted by a bard as he proclaims he is &quot;teh leet bard and owntz all bards&quot; this just makes it too simple to twist.
<br />

<br />
I do like song cast duration reduction tho... something like 2.8 or 2.9 cast time, small change it may be but that would be enough for me at least to never have a song drop unless there was some kind of severe lag.  Generally I never have an issue keeping 4 songs up, unless there is lag.
<br />

<br />
My issue that I have disliked for some time now is seeing song effect, then seeing song drop in text right below it and seeing the the song I just sung dropped.  I don't know if you would call that lag, some might, others might call it a bug. (I have referred to lag on songs dropping being cast bar completes, no song text/effect for a few seconds).
<br />

<br />
Im sure most of this post sounds jumbled... at work alt tabbing in and out of posting lol.</span></td>
