				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Wouldn't really work =/<a name="62330"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 16 04 6:02 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can remap your keyboard to something more comfortable, which is the real cure for KTS. My spell gems are mapped to q-w-e-a-s-d-f-x (added g with the 9th one). Which lets my left hand sit in the home position as I type aa-ss-dd-ee. I can keep that up all night with no twinges, no problem keeping four songs up. By keeping them grouped (rather than spread out along the number keys) all my songs are left hand while movement and targetting are right hand. It isn't a strech to hit mezz (q), slow (f), cure (x if I have it up). I put clickies in 1, 2 and 3. 3 is especially good if it's part of the twist e3e is easy.
<br />

<br />
I know this setup isn't for everyone. But I'm a touch typist and spend all day at the keyboard, so it works for me. Just find something comfortable. Minimize the movement. And make sure you're not looking at your keyboard. If you are, your setup is too hard.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
