				<td colspan="2"><span>I havent seen anyone mention how I have my hotkeys set up.  its only a few extra steps to include a   /stop   line and then puy the   /cast#   line in.  This way you only have to hit the key once for it to start fresh after the previous song
<br />
________________
<br />
name of hotkey1   
<br />
------------------
<br />
/stop                  
<br />
------------------
<br />
/cast 1
<br />
-------------------
<br />
_________________
<br />
name of hotkey2
<br />
--------------------
<br />
/stop
<br />
--------------------
<br />
/cast 2
<br />
--------------------
<br />
Etc etc..
<br />

<br />
when all keys are set up you can jusy go right down the line tapping the keys once and moving to the next,
<br />
and just an fyi..on perfect days I can sing 5 songs using this setup, and thats how including the song from the epic, or from vots, or from Amplify.
<br />

<br />
It's a lot less stressfull on the fingers during ang type of extended play, and becasue yout fingers move just a bit, most og keyboard is open to talk with.
<br />

<br />
I hope that helps a few of you out there
<br />

<br />
Rayin O'Hope
<br />
Lv 66 Bard
<br />
Rodcet Nife
<br />
