				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: An idea to ease four song twisting<a name="62604"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 17 04 9:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sorry to bore you...
<br />
When a song has a duration of 3 ticks, it means it will be active from cast till the server ticked 3 times... The server ticks every 6 seconds. So when you are lucky your song lands right after a server tick. and it looks like this:
<br />
*tick* [song lands] --6secs-- *tick* --6secs-- *tick* --6secs-- *tick and [song off]*
<br />
Thats a song duration of 18 seconds at max. Cast time is 3 secs so theoretically if your computer was server snychronised and everything was perfect (no time lost by stopping songs, reaction, missed notes etc.) 6 songs could be twisted. Practically 6 songs cant be twisted.
<br />
Now if you are unlucky your song lands right before a server tick, in this case it would look like this:
<br />
[song lands] *tick* --6secs-- *tick*  --6secs-- *tick [song off]*
<br />
In this case you would be left with 12 seconds song duration.
<br />
If there is no time at all lost due to lag, missd notes, human error etc., you can twist 4 songs even in the worst case of bd luck. However as there are things such as missed notes, lag etc, even when twisting 4 songs, a song will drop for a sec or 2 occassionally.
<br />
If you don't keep track of server ticks (doubt many if anyone does that), a 5 song twist can't be kept up reliably.
<br />
This is true for all 'normal' songs with a duration of 3 ticks  and no other mods of duration (like Warsong of the Vah Shir, Amplification etc.).
<br />
You can keep up 4 songs reasonably well. How often you drop one for a few secs depends on your connection, your PC, your luck with server ticks and to a minor degree on your fingers.
<br />
Think this should take care of the 'I can twist X songs' tales.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
@Brumm:
<br />
Firstly, when you realise you have a bad day, why post on a message board? I'd advise to have a cup of tea and take a bath instead...
<br />
Secondly, you should <i>never ever</i> say anyone sounds like an idiot, especially not when that 'idiot' is stating something correct.
<br />
By the way, I doubt twisting another Amplification and Kattas will give the twisting more quality. A solid 4 song twist of WoZ, PoV, CotM and CoM will be of more use than a dropping 6 song twist with PoV amped and a dex buff when everyone has maxed dex anyway...
<br />
In my opinion you are the easier target.
<br />
Not meant to be a flame, just please try to be more polite, even when you are having a bad day, thanks.
<br />
</span></td>
