			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: An idea to ease four song twisting<a name="62733"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 17 04 2:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Using long running songs like Amp, warsong and katta it is possible to go through two 6 song twists without dropping a necessary song.
<br />

<br />
amp
<br />
warsong
<br />
&lt;song 1&gt; (voice song to be amped)
<br />
&lt;song 2&gt;
<br />
&lt;song 3&gt;
<br />
&lt;song 4&gt;  &lt;--- 6 songs going
<br />
&lt;song 1&gt; 
<br />
&lt;song 2&gt;
<br />
(amp fades)
<br />
&lt;warsong&gt;
<br />
&lt;song 3&gt;
<br />
&lt;song 4&gt;  (this may fade 50/50 depending on missed notes etc - I usually make this chorus or a dot so I dont miss the benefit as it happens only on a tick and it will catch the next tick)
<br />

<br />
After this you can only do 5 including warsong.  You will drop a song every now and again but it will be back up by the next tick.  Fortunately most single encounters are over by the time this is sung twice (about 20 - 25 sec because I spin up before the mob gets to the camp).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
